A Python encoder for the Free Lossless Audio Codec

Requires Python 3 and some packages. Get started in two steps:

1. Install the requirements:

    $ pip3 install -r requirements.txt

2. Run it:

    $ python3 encode.py input_file.wav output_file.flac

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I'm writing this encoder to help me understand FLAC in intricate detail. The
implementation prioritizes simplicity over performance, so if you find this code
easy to understand then I've done my job. If you want a fast and robust
implementation, have a look at the reference encoder
(http://flac.sourceforge.net).

For simplicity, the encoder only supports 16-bit 44.1 kHz stereo wave input.
